  "summary": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/25/clermont-ferrands-cathedral-is-built-entirely-from-black-lava-stone.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Clermont-Ferrand&#039;s cathedral is built entirely from black lava stone\"><img alt=\"Portal of the Notre-Dame-de-l&#039;Assomption Cathedral in Clermont-Ferrand, France, built in black Volvic stone (HJBC/shutterstock.com)\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/cathedral.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p>The <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clermont-Ferrand_Cathedral\">Cathédrale Notre-Dame-de-l'Assomption</a> isn't just any old example of Gothic architecture. It screams gothic in striking, volcanic black. Situated in Clermont-Ferrand in France's Auvergne region, It is built entirely from black Volvic lava stone, a volcanic trachyandesite quarried from nearby sources.&#160",
